    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. WATCH How do astronauts go to the toilet in space?      WATCH: The law of gravity in space      WATCH: How do astronauts get water in space?      According to Thomas, a full orbit around earth while in a space shuttle is 90 minutes. In a 24 hour ‘day’, astronauts would see 16 sunrises and 16 sunsets while in orbit. At least 45 minutes of exercise on a bicycle in the space shuttle is a daily requirement to ensure the body does not lose function. While performing the mandatory exercise an astronaut would have passed half the globe. 12-year-old, TJ Shezi, was called to the stage to try on space gear. WATCH: KZN Pupil tries on astronaut space gear     Shezi told the Sunday Tribune, that after the seminar he would do everything possible to be an astronaut when he grows up, including doing his math homework each day.  SUNDAY TRIBUNE